title: Windows: Time service (w32time) peer summary status
agents: windows
catalog: os/services
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the configured time synchronization peers in the Windows
 time service (w32time) as a singular summary service.

 A ruleset, "Windows time service peers summary" exists where alerting can be
 configured in multiple ways, e.g., reporting on when a peer's stratum changes,
 when the last several consecutive attempts to communicate with the peer have
 failed, or  when some number of attempts out of the last (not necessarily
 consecutive) tries to contact the server have failed. See the help text in the
 ruleset for more information.

 If the service is configured to only alert if all hosts cross the defined
 thresholds, then the service status will only change if every peer would
 otherwise be in WARN or CRIT state, and the worst state will be reflected
 as the service state.

discovery:
 One summary service is created. If you wish to have one service per peer, use
 the {NTP Discovery} ruleset on this host to configure that.
